{
  "stem": "10587.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Mark, M-A-R-K, Bader, B-A-D-E-R.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At birth I was given the name of Moses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Polish, it's [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Moises. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Bader.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Bader was always my name and still is.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, they called me [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Moisela. ?] They called me [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Moniac ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- they most-- mostly these two names.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and my real name, which was always [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Moniac ?], but in cheder I was called by my Yiddish name.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in-- in school I was called by my given name, Polish name.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was a Polish name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that on the birth certificate would probably be [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Moises ?] Bader.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in the city of Oswiecim, which during the war was renamed by the Germans to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Poland.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the borders changed quite often.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "During my time it was-- belonged to Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, my father was a-- was living in the same area, [INAUDIBLE], which is just maybe 30 to 35 kilometers away from Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was, during World War I, he was in the Austrian army.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was an officer in the Austrian army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it interchanged quite often.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My birth date is April 25, 1927.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- since I lived in Oswiecim, this was the birthplace of my mother, which dates back to the-- the-- the maiden name was Enoch, E-N-O-C-H.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Enoch family dates back to the 16th century in the city of Oswiecim, which at that time must have been Austria.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] During-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] when I was a-- a little boy, when I went to school and to cheder, Oswiecim was a peaceful little town.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were quite a few-- I had quite a few friends with a large family, lot of cousins, uncles and aunts.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was a tranquil type of a community, even so that we always felt that the anti-Semitism was always present, from-- coming from the Poles, from non-Jew Poles.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but we didn't have much trouble with it because they-- everyone of the city was-- knew the name Enoch because of-- we were-- since it was a very old, established name.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also my grandfather had a hardware store in-- in center of town, which was right in the main centrum, in the main square.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I used to horse around quite a bit with my younger brother, and we were always very happy and-- and disruptive, to the point where my mother named me Haman.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And every time I'm used to come back from school, or from cheder, she says-- she used to say, run for your life, Haman is coming.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Unfortunately, my younger brother was killed in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He never survived the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The 17-- my-- the Bader family, which actually in Poland it was pronounced 'Bah-der.' They-- they dated back to the 17th century in Wadowice My grandfather Jacob and Tamara Bader were my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had quite a few uncles and aunts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were like, I think, 10 children, many cousins and uncles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A big family.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I used to visit Wadowice quite often, especially during vacation time when school was out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at home, we were six children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were a very happy bunch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We always [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] waited for the-- for Sabbath, for Shabbos, for the Saturday, because my mother used to bake quite a few cakes, various types of cakes like streuselkuchen, and moon cake, cheesecake, and maybe four or five different cakes.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And every Saturday morning, we would eat in bed with-- so we would have the cakes, variety of cakes, and we used to gorge ourselves on it with milk.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then I used to, with my father, to-- to the temple.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We had a beautiful temple in-- in the city of Oswiecim, which the Germans destroyed, I think.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It must have been in 1940 or maybe beginning of '41, because when I became bar mitzvah, I remember the temple was no longer there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They burned it one day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my bar mitzvah took place in-- in a basement, when people were standing guard to make sure that the Germans would not find us, because it was against the law to congregate, or to have a group of people together.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I remember that I worked very hard to do a good job, but it-- it was-- it was in a-- in-- in the basement of the-- of my grandfather's house.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] The-- we-- most of the family lived in my grandfather's building.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Each child used to have their own apartment, and own their own apartment.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was a-- a large complex of buildings like a square itself.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
